results.title: Discovering new cancer treatments in the 'dark matter' of the human genome
results.description: Cancer is the second leading cause of death in Switzerland. Among the different types of cancers, non-small cell lung cancer (NSCLC) kills the most patients and remains largely incurable. Unfortunately, even newly approved therapies can extend the life of patients by only a few months and only few survive the metastatic stadium long-term. Thus, new treatments that attack the cancer in novel ways are sought.

results.title: Police release more details about a collision in South Lethbridge
results.description: LETHBRIDGE, AB - The Lethbridge Police Service Traffic Response Unit has released more information about a collision between two vehicles that occurre...
results.content: LETHBRIDGE, AB – The Lethbridge Police Service Traffic Response Unit has released more information about a collision between two vehicles that occurred on October 5, 2022 at the intersection of Mayor Magrath Drive South and 26 Avenue South. According to the Traffic Response Unit, a vehicle travelling southbound on Mayor Magrath Drive was turning east onto 26 Avenue when it was struck by a vehicle travelling northbound on Mayor Magrath, resulting in the southbound vehicle ending up in the ditch on the east side of Mayor Magrath Drive. Police say the 89-year-old driver of the southbound vehicle was able to free himself from the vehicle, but the 49-year-old female passenger needed assistance from Lethbridge Fire and Emergency Services. Both were taken to hospital with non-life-threatening injuries. The driver of the northbound vehicle, a 49-year-old male, was not injured in the collision. Lethbridge police are continuing their investigation and say they will provide an update when more information becomes available.
